We’ve built some 900 new kindergartens for 270,000 children. We are changing the face of Israeli education, knowing that education is the spearhead of science, technology and a strong economy.

Let me remind all of you that this change represents a savings to parents of NIS 800 a month per child -- an enormous savings for families. But not only does this constitute our contribution to the future of our children; we are doing this at a time when economies all over the world are contracting, because we know that this is the best investment that we can make in our country’s future.
